                  "LCS"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A laser Compton back-scattering (LCS). The LCS",
                "gamma-beam was generated with almost 100% circularly",
                "polarized photons with an energy of 2.475 MeV and an",
                "average flux of approximately 3x10**5 gamma/s/keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High-purity Germanium (HPGe) detector array."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Four different thicknesses of 238U, namely 1.287,",
                "2.703, 4.117 and 5.563 mm consisted of 2, 4, 6 and 8",
                "foils, respectively. Eight disks of depleted uranium",
                " (DU), which has a density of 19.1 g cm-3. Each disk",
                "of DU is 25.4mm in diameter and approximately 0.6 mm",
                "in thickness with a mass of approximately 6.5 g, and",
                "each disk is encased within a thin plastic sealant."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The HIgammaS facility is based on the Compton",
                "backscattering of free electron-laser (FEL) photons",
                "with electrons stored in the storage ring. Nuclear",
                "Resonance Fluorescence (NRF): The scattering NRF",
                "gamma-ray spectra were collected with an HPGe",
                "detector array with a total hours on-beam of LCS",
                "gamma-ray source of 32.5 h. This work is based on the",
                "atomic and nuclear absorption of the incident and/or",
                "scattered NRF gamma-rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Mostly statistical uncertainties.",
                "Attenuation factors helped to avoid many systematic",
                "errors that occur in the NRF experiments, such as the",
                "flux measurements and the detector detection",
                "efficiency."
              ]
            }
